-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The sigrok project aims at creating a portable, cross-platform,
Free/Libre/Open-Source logic analyzer software that supports various
logic analyzer hardware products.

sigrok-qt is a Qt-based GUI for sigrok.


Status
------

The sigrok-qt project is currently work in progress. Some basic functionality
is there, but it should still be considered alpha/beta stage software.


Requirements
------------

 - git
 - g++
 - make
 - libtool
 - pkg-config >= 0.22
 - libglib >= 2.22.0
 - Qt >= 4.5
 - libsigrok >= 0.2.0
 - libsigrokdecode >= 0.1.0


Building and installing
-----------------------

In order to get the sigrok-qt source code and build it, run:

 $ git clone git://sigrok.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/sigrok/sigrok
 $ cd sigrok/sigrok-qt
 $ qmake
 $ make

For installing sigrok-qt:

 $ make install

Please see the following wiki pages for more detailed instructions:

 http://sigrok.org/wiki/Linux
 http://sigrok.org/wiki/Mac_OS_X
 http://sigrok.org/wiki/Windows
 http://sigrok.org/wiki/FreeBSD


Mailing lists
-------------

There are two mailing lists for sigrok/sigrok-qt:

 https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/sigrok-devel
 https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/sigrok-commits


IRC
---

You can find the sigrok developers in the #sigrok IRC channel on Freenode.


Website
-------

http://sigrok.org

